72.6	Anton_Corbijn	Anton Corbijn	Anton Corbijn (Dutch pronunciation: ; born 20 May 1955) is a Dutch photographer, music video and film director. He is the creative director behind the visual output of Depeche Mode and U2, having handled the principal promotion and sleeve photography for both for almost 3 decades. Some of his works include music videos for Depeche Mode's "Enjoy the Silence" (1990) and Nirvana's "Heart-Shaped Box" (1993), as well as the Ian Curtis biopic Control (2007), George Clooney's The American (2010), and A Most Wanted Man (2012) based on John le Carr√©'s 2008 novel of the same name.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Anton_Corbijn_%28Berlinale_2012%29.jpg/185px-Anton_Corbijn_%28Berlinale_2012%29.jpg
